 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Scalar field collapse in a conformally flat spacetime</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">Springer</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">The collapse scenario of a scalar field along with a perfect fluid distribution was investigated for a conformally flat spacetime. The theorem for the integrability of an anharmonic oscillator has been utilized. For a pure power-law potential of the form ${\phi }^{n+1}$ , it was found that a central singularity is formed which is covered by an apparent horizon for $n&gt;0$ and $n&lt;-3$ . Some numerical results have also been presented for a combination of two different powers of $\phi $ in the potential.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">Springer</subfield>
 </datafield>
